## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
- ❌ Don't hardcode exit code 3 — use ui.ExitRescue.
- ❌ Don't os.Exit inside handleSignal (breaks unit tests) — keep the pure core exit-free; exit via the seam in the goroutine.
- ❌ Don't restore AFTER UpdateRefCAS (Gotcha #1 — work-item + PRD §18.4 say BEFORE).
- ❌ Don't gate TREE inside the handler with extra params — signature is fixed; gate inside the rescueFn closure.
- ❌ Don't arm the handler before WriteTree (pre-snapshot SIGINT must use Go default → exit 130).
- ❌ Don't create a stub CommitStaged in this task (that is P1.M6.T1.S1).
- ❌ Don't add testify or external deps (codebase is stdlib-only).
